<div class="sd2-genuine__intro"><div><p>Counterfeit and imitation parts can resemble Sinister Diesel&reg; products in photos, descriptions and color while lacking the materials, fit and support of a genuine part.</p><p>Use the checks below before installation. If you see or suspect a counterfeit product, email <a href="mailto:brandprotection@sinisterdiesel.com">brandprotection@sinisterdiesel.com</a>.</p></div><figure><mvt:item name="readytheme" param="image( 'identifying-genuine-sinister-parts' )" /><figcaption>Compare markings, finish and packaging before installation.</figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="sd2-genuine__checks"><article><span>01 / Finish</span><h2>Look for Sinister Blue.</h2><p>With limited special-edition exceptions, genuine Sinister Diesel hard parts use the recognizable Sinister Blue finish.</p></article><article><span>02 / Part mark</span><h2>Find the product logo.</h2><p>Genuine parts carry a visible etched, engraved or printed Sinister Diesel logo appropriate to the product.</p></article><article><span>03 / Packaging</span><h2>Inspect the box and seal.</h2><p>Look for current Sinister Diesel branding on the packaging or sealing materials and verify the product code.</p></article><article><span>04 / Price</span><h2>Question extreme discounts.</h2><p>A price far below established market pricing can be a warning sign. Compare the offer with current direct and authorized-dealer pricing.</p></article><article><span>05 / Seller</span><h2>Use an authorized dealer.</h2><p>Verify that the seller is an authorized Sinister Diesel dealer and provides a traceable purchase record.</p></article><article><span>06 / Source</span><h2>Buy direct when unsure.</h2><p>Purchasing directly from Sinister Diesel provides the clearest authenticity, warranty and support path.</p></article></div>
